                             ³SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS³
                             ÀÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÙ

þ Shadow Warrior's minimum system requirements are:

  A Pentium with 16 megabytes of memory and VGA graphics.  A CD-ROM is required
  for the registered version.

  We strongly recommend a Pentium 90 with more than 16 megs of memory and PCI
  Local Bus Video (at least 2Mb of Video Memory), for optimal
  performance.

  For the SVGA modes, a VESA compliant video card is required.  Please see your
  video card's manual for info on how to find out if your card is VESA
  compliant.  If yours is not VESA compliant, you will need to use a software
  driver to provide this compliance.  We suggest a driver such as Display
  Doctor (formerly called UniVBE).  If you have the registered CD-ROM of Shadow
  Warrior, Display Doctor can be found on the CD-ROM in the \goodies\univbe
  directory. If you have the shareware version of Shadow Warrior, you must
  obtain Univbe on your own.  It can be obtained at any of 3D Realms' online
  support forums (See "3D Realms Online" at the bottom of this document for
  contact information).  It can also be obtained directly from the program's
  author (SciTech Software) at http://www.scitechsoft.com. To install Univbe,
  copy the files from the \goodies\univbe directory on the CD-ROM to a
  temporary directory on your hard drive, change to that directory, and type
  "INSTALL".

  NOTE: There are no versions of Shadow Warrior that have been optimized for
        any specific video cards, chipsets, or VR devices from 3D Realms. If
        such a version exists, it would have to have come from the people that
        make your particular card/device.  Please contact them.

þ For game play, the following devices are optionally supported: Keyboard,
  Mouse, Joystick, Gravis GamePad, Flightstick, & ThrustMaster/Wingman.

þ The following sound cards/devices are also optionally supported:

  For Music: Gravis UltraSound, Sound Blaster (all of them), SoundMan16,
             Pro Audio Spectrum, SoundScape, WaveBlaster, Sound Canvas,
             Adlib, and General MIDI.

  For SFX: Sound Blaster (all of them), Gravis UltraSound, SoundMan16,
           Pro Audio Spectrum, SoundScape, Disney/Tandy Sound Sources.

  There is no support for the PC Speaker.


