  may be to purchase one.  The reason for this is that most newer systems run
  at a speed that is several orders of magnitude faster than your port can send
  data.  In short, your system is outrunning your game port, and Shadow Warrior
  can't see what the port is sending since it doesn't come in fast enough.
  Fortunately, speed adjustable ports such as the Gravis Eliminator or JDR
  Microdevices' MCT Micro-III are inexpensive solutions to this problem. (Note:
  3D Realms does not endorse any of these products - they are listed here only
  as examples of what is available.)
