A network isn't something to find, or something you can share with your
friends in other towns, and it doesn't involve just living in the same area. A
network consists of a series of computers with network cards that physically
link the computers by a network cable.  To network your systems together, all
the computers would have to be in the same room or building.  The greater the
distance (up to 300ft) increases the cost of the cable. You can find cards for
around $20 each and cable will run from $15 for a 50ft patch cable to $130 for
500ft. roll that you can cut for the desired length. If you need more info,
check out a book from your library or book store like "LAN for dummies".   It
explains it in plain English.

Here is a short summary of how to play a network game.  A more detailed
explanation will follow.

1) Run the setup program.  Once in the setup program, select "Network Game".
2) Alter any of the options you wish, and then select "Launch Shadow Warrior".
3) Once all the players are found, the game will load.  Once the game is at
   the Main Menu, select "New Game".
4) If you are Player 1, you will choose the game options.  All other players
   will have to wait for Player 1 to select the game options.
5) If you are player 1, select the difficulty, level, etc, and select "Begin
   Play".  You're in!

